<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Paramere quadrangle-shaped in lateral view, with ca 3 sensillae medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Scaptodrosophila serrateifoliacea sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416846" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">11C, D</figureCitation>
); gonopods developed, arm-shaped, with many finely acanthoid processes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Scaptodrosophila serrateifoliacea sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416846" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">11C, D</figureCitation>
); aedeagus beanpod-shaped in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Scaptodrosophila serrateifoliacea sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416846" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">11C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
(♂, ♀) 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. serrateifoliacea sp. nov. B, D, F S. sinuata sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416840" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5A</figureCitation>
): Frons yellowish brown. Pedicel yellow. First flagellomere yellowish. Facial carina yellowish, short, 1/2 length as face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. serrateifoliacea sp. nov. B, D, F S. sinuata sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416840" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5C, E</figureCitation>
): Mesonotum and scutellum dark brown. Acrostichal setulae in ca 8 irregular rows. Halter yellowish brown. Wings hazel.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. serrateifoliacea sp. nov. B, D, F S. sinuata sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416840" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5C, E</figureCitation>
): First tergite and second tergite yellow. Third to sixth tergites brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male terminalia</emphasis>
: Epandrium with ca 19 setae near posterior margin and ventral corner on each side (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Scaptodrosophila serrateifoliacea sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416846" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">11A, B</figureCitation>
). Surstylus broad, with ca 10 fine peg-like prensisetae on caudal margin, and numerous setae on outer and inner surfaces (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Scaptodrosophila serrateifoliacea sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416846" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">11A, B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium pubescent near paramedian setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Scaptodrosophila serrateifoliacea sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416846" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">11C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Female terminalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Scaptodrosophila serrateifoliacea sp. nov. ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416846" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">11E</figureCitation>
): Oviscapt with 1 long subapical trichoid ovisensillum on ventral margins and densely covered with peg-like ovisensilla.
</paragraph>
