<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
A combination of the Latin words &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">serratus</emphasis>
&quot; (= serrated) + &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">foliaceus</emphasis>
&quot; (= folium), referring to the gonopods with numerous finely serrated processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
